<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,654,1218]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,654,679]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Characters of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1900" box="[479,577,654,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aturidae</taxonomicName>
and the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[791,943,654,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Axonopsinae">Axonopsinae</taxonomicName>
. Dorsal and ventral shields anteriorly fused; dorsal shield with seven pairs of glandularia and a pair of postocularia. Venter without a ridge on each side extending posteriorly from the region of insertion of the IV-L. Two pairs of glandularia lying between the genital field and insertions of the IV-L, relatively close together in male; posterior pair halfway between the fist pair of glandularia and genital field in female. Genital field with three pairs of so-called wheel-like acetabula; II-, III- and IV-L with swimming setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
